  "text": "DIG-labeled RNA probes were prepared according to the protocols described by [CITATION_1] . Templates for riboprobe synthesis were amplified, with an M13 primer set, from the plasmids containing cDNA fragments of Ttu-Bra (nt 829-1498 bp). An antisense and sense riboprobes were synthesized with T7 and T3 RNA polymerases, respectively. Whole-mount in situ hybridization was performed according to the method described previously [CITATION_2] with slight modifications. Hybridization (60-72 h) and subsequent wash were both performed at 55°C.",
